{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> σταθμ-ίον</b> <br /> or <b>στάθμιον</b>, τό, <i>diminutive</i> (in form) of σταθμός 111, <b>weight of a balance</b>, variant in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἀγμῶν” 8. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> a specific weight of wool, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PTeb.” 116.23, 26 (2nd c.BC), 117.17 (1st c.BC). \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>standard weight</b>, σ., ἃ ὁ δῆμος σηκῶσαι ἐψηφίσαντο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 22.1388.46, +others, cf. LXX.Lev.19.35, +others\">LXX</a>]; <b>balance</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Vit.Auct.” 27, 2nd c.AD: Sextus Empiricus Philosophus “adversus Mathematicos” 7.27 (and so perhaps in [same places] above). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>plummet</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.2Ki.21.13. \">LXX</a>]","strongNumber":"G9149","accentedUnicode":"στάθμιον","shortDef":"a scale-weight","mediumDef":"a scale-weight","stepGloss":"a scale-weight","stepTransliteration":"stathmion","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}